theorem closure_inter_closure_compl_eq_closure_diff_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (A : Set X) ∩ closure ((A : Set X)ᶜ) =
      closure (A : Set X) \ interior A := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    have hNotInt : x ∉ interior (A : Set X) := by
      intro hxInt
      -- Obtain an open neighborhood `U ⊆ A` with `x ∈ U`.
      rcases mem_interior.1 hxInt with ⟨U, hUsub, hUopen, hxU⟩
      -- Since `x ∈ closure (Aᶜ)`, `U` must meet `Aᶜ`, a contradiction.
      have hNon : ((U : Set X) ∩ ((A : Set X)ᶜ)).Nonempty :=
        (mem_closure_iff).1 hx.2 U hUopen hxU
      rcases hNon with ⟨y, ⟨hyU, hyCompl⟩⟩
      exact hyCompl (hUsub hyU)
    exact ⟨hx.1, hNotInt⟩
  · intro hx
    have hClA : x ∈ closure (A : Set X) := hx.1
    have hClCompl : x ∈ closure ((A : Set X)ᶜ) := by
      -- Show that every open neighborhood of `x` meets `Aᶜ`.
      refine (mem_closure_iff).2 ?_
      intro U hUopen hxU
      by_contra hEmpty
      -- `U` is disjoint from `Aᶜ`, hence `U ⊆ A`.
      have hUSubA : (U : Set X) ⊆ A := by
        intro y hy
        by_contra hyCompl
        have : (U : Set X) ∩ ((A : Set X)ᶜ) ≠ ∅ := by
          exact ⟨y, ⟨hy, hyCompl⟩⟩
        exact hEmpty this
      -- Therefore `x ∈ interior A`, contradicting `x ∉ interior A`.
      have : x ∈ interior (A : Set X) :=
        mem_interior.2 ⟨U, hUSubA, hUopen, hxU⟩
      exact (hx.2 this).elim
    exact ⟨hClA, hClCompl⟩

theorem closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure (A : Set X) := by
  -- First inclusion: `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`.
  have h₁ :
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
    exact closure_mono (interior_subset : (interior (closure (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
  -- Second inclusion: `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
  have h₂ :
      closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
    -- Because `A` is open, it is contained in `interior (closure A)`.
    have hsub :
        (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (A : Set X)) :=
      interior_maximal (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A) hA
    exact closure_mono hsub
  exact le_antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem closure_union_interior_self {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure ((A : Set X) ∪ interior A) = closure (A : Set X) := by
  have h : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ A := interior_subset
  have hUnion : (A : Set X) ∪ interior A = A :=
    Set.union_eq_self_of_subset_right h
  simpa [hUnion]
